      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/couette-flow-hemolysis-calibration",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law calibration against Couette-flow hemolysis data",
      "description": "The hemolysis power-law model (dHb/Hb = C * tau^alpha * t^beta) was calibrated and validated against published Couette-flow experimental datasets. Predicted hemolysis index values agreed with measured values within 12% across the calibration range (shear stress 50–400 Pa, exposure time 0.01–1.0 s). The model is considered valid under the theoretical precondition that the power-law relationship is linear in log-space within the calibration regime.",
      "passed": true,
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute relative error 9.3% across 48 Couette-flow data points"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/pump-pressure-head-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD pump pressure-head and flow-rate validation against bench test data",
      "description": "Simulated pump pressure-head versus flow-rate curves were compared against experimental measurements on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump across 3 rotational speeds (2000, 2500, 3500 RPM). Predicted values fell within 8% of measured values at all operating points. Turbulence model (SST k-omega) reproduced the recirculation zone extent qualitatively consistent with PIV measurements.",
      "passed": true,
      "quantitativeMetric": "Maximum pressure-head deviation 7.6%; mean 4.1% across 15 operating points"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/mesh-independence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence study for hemolysis index predictions",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1M, 5.4M, 11.8M cells) were evaluated. The hemolysis index changed by less than 3% between the medium and fine meshes, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2.",
      "passed": true,
      "quantitativeMetric": "GCI < 2.8% between medium and fine mesh for hemolysis index QoI"
    }
  ],
