      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented with sufficient detail to confirm relevance to the COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Bench test data for pressure-head validation were collected at flow rates 2–6 L/min and rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, spanning the CPB operating envelope. Temperature (37°C), fluid viscosity (blood analogue, 3.5 cP), and inlet boundary conditions are documented in the test report."
