      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modeled QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the clinical decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = HI_device / HI_predicate. This metric is directly used in the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and is computed from CFD-derived hemolysis index values. The linkage between QoI and decision criterion is explicit and documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
