      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2. Analysts hold documented CFD training credentials and followed a standard operating procedure for simulation setup and post-processing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The chosen turbulence and hemolysis sub-models must be justified as appropriate for the flow physics of the COU. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is applied under the theoretical precondition that its log-linear stress-exposure relationship remains valid across the turbulent recirculating regimes of the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is selected based on its established performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model (dHb/Hb = C * tau^alpha * t^beta, with alpha=1.9918, beta=0.6606) is adopted as the standard sub-model for blood pump hemolysis prediction. The model is theoretically valid under the assumption that the power-law relationship is linear in log-space across the full range of shear stress and exposure time encountered in the device. This precondition was established from Couette-flow experiments at moderate shear rates and is assumed to extend to the high-shear, turbulent recirculating flow zones characteristic of the CPB pump operating envelope. Model form is assessed as adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, boundary conditions, fluid properties) must be traceable to documented sources and representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry is based on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump CAD files (publicly available). Boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed) are set to the 5 flow-speed combinations defined in the COU. Blood viscosity and density are set to standard values for 37°C human blood. All inputs are documented in the simulation input deck archived with this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
