    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 framework. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is accepted as the standard hemolysis sub-model, with its theoretical precondition (log-linear stress-exposure relationship) noted in the model form rationale. The relative hemolysis index predictions satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all 5 operating conditions evaluated.",
